description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using version 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I suspect it may be related to a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println('Hello');
       }
   }
2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc -d subpackage subpackage/Test.java

Observed Behavior:
When compiling the class, a directory 'subpackage' is created under the existing 'subpackage' directory.

Expected Behavior:
The compiled class should be placed in the existing 'subpackage' directory, without creating a subdirectory with the same name.
